#week-title("One", "Philosophy of the Philosophic Mercury")

=== Core Teaching

The Philosophic Mercury is not a symbol only — it is a material substance that
can be prepared, worked with, and used as a universal solvent.

In the vegetable kingdom, the philosophic mercury was the rectified spirit of
wine. In the water work, the philosophic mercury is the purified, potentized
water itself. Collected, fermented, distilled, and circulated, this water
concentrates its universal virtue until it becomes a bridge between the
vegetable and mineral worlds.

#doctrine[
  _"Salts serve as 'magnets' for subtle forces, which then become available for
  the laboratory. The water work lies at the borderline between the kingdoms —
  an intermediate zone that trains the practitioner in working with forces that
  are neither fixed nor fully volatile."_
  #align(right)[— Robert Allen Bartlett, _Real Alchemy_]
]

=== Topics This Week

- Defining the Philosophic Mercury in water
- Water as the universal solvent for the intermediate zone
- The relationship between salts and subtle forces

#inner-work[
  *The Spirit of Mercury*

  Contemplate the quality of "spirit." In your laboratory, it is the volatile.
  In your mind, it is that which connects the body (structure) to the soul
  (character).

  How does the "spirit" of water differ from the "spirit" of wine? Record your
  philosophical comparisons in your journal.
]

